cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.HC 

This paper focuses on analyzing the quality and impact of content on social investment platforms, using sentiment analysis and correlation with stock performance. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) due to the use of sentiment analysis tools. Additionally, the paper discusses user interactions and behavior, which could fall under the sub-categories of Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper also touches on the topic of stock manipulation, which could be related to the sub-category of Security and Privacy (cs.SEC).
